> From your previous message, you say you have a carb? What happened to your
> fuel injection?
> If you had FI, you would have a rubber hose going from the tank to the drivers
> side frame rail. There are 2
> plastic clips mounted to the floor for the hose to sit in.
> The 7.5mm hose goes to the filter, then a short piece of 10mm hose connects
> between the filter and the FI
> pump. Then a short piece of 7.5 hose goes between the pump and the metal fuel
> rail connected to the 3/4
> injectors.
> If you have a modified fuel system, no one can tell you what you have unless
> they see it....

My FI bus has two more pieces:

* This metal piece from the tank to the filter...

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/FuelHose/02-TankToFuelPump.JPG

* This metal piece that goes after the pump. It connects to a very short
piece of hose that connects to the 1/2 fuel rail which protrudes through the
firewall.

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/FuelHose/01-PumpToFuelRail.JPG


